ent when the climate threatens populations who live closest to nature--and depend upon its fodder for heat, its water for life, and its seeds for food--Mallick shows how nonviolent action can give poor people an effective voice.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aEnvironmentalismzIndia. 0aSocial movementszIndia. 4aAsian Studies. 4aEnvironment and Sustainability. 4aFood Studies. 4aPolitics and Government. 4aSociology and Social History. 4aSouth Asia. 7aNATURE / Environmental Conservation & Protection.2bisacsh  aEnvironmental movements of India, Environmental Justice, Sustainability, Women's issues, Nonviolence, Gandhian Satyagraha.1 aLappé, Frances, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311074322708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2z978311074335708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2021 Englishz978311075414808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2021z9783110753912oZDB-23-DPM40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978904853509540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048535095423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048535095/original  a978-3-11-074322-7  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-074335-7  DG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075414-8  EBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2021 Eng